The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 IFA officials hinted on Saturday that the I-League matches scheduled on September 28 and October 3 might be postponed by a day, as matches on those dates might cause inconvenience to the West Bengal police.       
	According to current fixtures, Mohammedan Sporting are slated to face Air India at the Barasat stadium on September 28, while Air India are to play Mohun Bagan on October 3.                
	 Rittika Kundu and Srijani Dey won their semi-final ties on Saturday in the nursery girls category at the B.M. Chattoraj Memorial Table Tennis Championship. In the cadet girls segment, Riya Datta and Rupsa Bango reached the final.       
	Rittika won her semi-final match in the sub-junior section as well, beating Pallabi Guha, while Rupsa lost to Sagarika Mukherjee.                      
	TABLE TENNIS: B.M. Chattoraj Memorial Championship at Rabindra Sarobar from 10 am                                                                                                                                                                     
